contract.contract_description: A Spiro is a one-of-a-kind work of art created from a spirograph on the blockchain. It is created from an algorithm that produces mathematical roulette curves to generate art. Not all Spiros are created equally. An incredibly scarce number of Spiros will be minted as `rare`. The spirograph algorithm, your sequence of numbers, and a rarity curve will determine the rare-ness of your Spiro. In addition to the `rare` quality, these Spiros are distinguished by their `color`. Rare Spiros can come in a range of colors with some being more scarce than others. The time at which you mint can improve your chances to get a `rare` Spiro due to our rarity curve.

name: [1e] 55555
description: First Edition Hashrune **#608**, uniquely generated from the name "**55555**" and stored on the blockchain. Minted on [Hashrunes.com](https://www.hashrunes.com).

contract.contract_description: **On-chain art, summoned by you.** Hashrunes are the **first on-chain named** pieces of generative art. The **name, design, and colors** of each Hashrune all live **completely on the blockchain**. Each **NFT** (non-fungible token) is born from the **unique name** given by its creator. No two Hashrunes are alike. Once a name is claimed, its Hashrune **can't** be minted again. Hashrunes are **very scarce** due to an increasing minting fee. There are two editions: **Genesis Hashrunes** are the original Hashrunes with a pure design. **First Edition Hashrunes** have a corner design that distinguishes them from Genesis Hashrunes. They have a maximum supply. Genesis owners can mint their First Edition versions for free (other people can't mint them). To mint, visit **[Hashrunes.com](https://www.hashrunes.com)**.
